      "tip": "The Bitterroot is taking its summer fishing shape. Riffle edges, tailouts, grassy banks, and soft bank seams are absolutely loaded with feeding fish. The trout are seeing a variety of bugs, making them active and willing to eat dry flies. Log jams and debris are still a major hazard especially with the watering dropping as fast as it is, so floaters need to stay alert. Float cautiously! Fishing in the morning and the evenings will be the best time to be on the water. Keep an eye on water temps in the afternoons as it is starting to get hotter.",
